# GitHub syntax highlighting for the decompiled CP/M assembly sources.
# Linguist already classifies .asm/.s as Assembly; these lines guarantee
# and normalize it (the generic Assembly grammar suits both the sjasmplus
# Z-80 .asm and ca65 6502 .s files, which use ; comments). Note GitHub has
# no 6502/Z-80-specific highlighter, so comments, labels, numbers, and
# directives color but mnemonics are not treated as keywords.
*.asm linguist-language=Assembly
*.s   linguist-language=Assembly
